Problem No : 04
Problem Name : Write a c program to calculate the summation of each digits of a large number.
Sample Input/Output :  Enter a large number :3ghbv45ff67

Total number of digits 5
Sum of digits 25
Process returned 0 (0x0)   execution time : 9.062 s
Press any key to continue.
Coding : 
#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
    char str[100];
    int i,c=0,sum=0;
    printf("Enter a large number :");
    scanf("%s",&str);
    for (i=0; str[i]!='\0'; i++)
    {
        if((str[i]>='0' && str[i]<='9'))
        {
           c++;
           sum+=(str[i]-'0');
        }
    }
printf("\nTotal number of digits %d",c);
printf("\nSum of digits %d",sum);
return 0;
}
Result and Discussion : From  the case analysis and the coding  the output and input is same .So , I can say that my code is all right. 




